  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Sahanivasa will utilize funds from GGF to promote biodiversity agriculture and to protect people and the environment from hazards presented by toxic chemicals related to thermal power plants and pesticide usage. Sahanivasa will work in collaboration with thirty organizations in Andhra Pradesh to strengthen the campaign against thermal power plants and toxic pesticides, with the goal to increase awareness of the dangers of these practices among community members. Sahanivasa will work with government officials to inform them of the need to monitor the inflow of banned hazardous pesticides sold in India. It will combat pesticide usage by promoting biodiversity methods of pest control in agricultural techniques. These efforts will be strengthened through close partnerships with national and international organizations.</narrative>
  </description>
